                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      FIR against IIT teacher 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Nov. 9: IIT Kharagpur has charged a professor with fraud after an internal inquiry indicted him for associating with a fake institute without taking the tech schools permission.         
	The IIT authorities have decided to file an FIR against A.K. Ghosh. It said a senior faculty members association with the Institution of Electrical Engineering (IEE), a fake institute, amounted to a case of fraud.         
	As per the code of conduct, a faculty cannot associate himself with any institute without the IITs permission. His association amounted to fraud, a source said.                                                                                                                                                           
